
[1]sastra

   SAS'TRA, n. Among the Hindoos, a sacred book; a book containing sacred
   ordinances. The six great Sastras, in the opinion of the Hindoos,
   contain all knowledge, human and divine. These are the Veda, Upaveda,
   Vedanga, Purana, Dherma, and Dersana.
